attributes.name: age
attributes.description: Age of the adult in years, ranging from 18 to 80.

attributes.name: gender
attributes.description: Self-identified gender of the individual (Male, Female, Non-binary/Other).

attributes.name: race_ethnicity
attributes.description: Racial and ethnic self-identification (White non-Hispanic, Black, Hispanic/Latino, Asian, Other/Multiracial).

attributes.name: us_region
attributes.description: US census region of residence (Northeast, Southeast, Midwest, Southwest, West Coast).

attributes.name: urban_rural
attributes.description: Urbanicity of the household's location (Urban, Suburban, Rural).

attributes.name: education_level
attributes.description: Highest educational attainment (Less than HS, HS diploma/GED, Some college, Bachelor's degree, Graduate degree).

attributes.name: household_income
attributes.description: Annual household income in USD before taxes.

attributes.name: marital_status
attributes.description: Current marital or partnership status (Married/partnered, Single, Divorced/separated, Widowed).

attributes.name: household_size
attributes.description: Total number of people living in the household.

attributes.name: has_children
attributes.description: Whether the individual has any children (under 18) living in the household.

attributes.name: employment_sector
attributes.description: Primary employment sector (Federal government, State/local government, Private sector, Gig/contract, Self-employed, Retired, Unemployed, Not in labor force).

attributes.name: job_security_perception
attributes.description: Perceived stability of current employment (Very secure, Somewhat secure, Somewhat insecure, Very insecure, N/A - not employed).

attributes.name: financial_margin
attributes.description: Financial buffer status indicating paycheck-to-paycheck living (Comfortable savings buffer, Modest buffer, Paycheck-to-paycheck, In debt/deficit).

attributes.name: investment_profile
attributes.description: Investment and financial literacy profile (No investments, 401k/IRA only, Diversified investor, Active trader, Crypto holder).

attributes.name: primary_info_source
attributes.description: Primary source of news and information (Cable/broadcast TV news, Social media, Online news sites, Podcasts, Local news, Print media, Avoids news).

attributes.name: social_media_behavior
attributes.description: Social media engagement posture (Non-user, Passive consumer, Occasional poster, Active poster/Influencer).

attributes.name: tech_adoption_posture
attributes.description: Attitude toward adopting new technology (Technophobe/Avoider, Late majority adopter, Early majority adopter, Early adopter, Innovator).

attributes.name: religious_engagement
attributes.description: Level of religious practice and belief (Secular/None, Nominally affiliated, Moderately religious, Devout).

attributes.name: political_identity
attributes.description: Political party affiliation and ideological strength (Strong Democrat, Lean Democrat, True Independent, Lean Republican, Strong Republican).

attributes.name: political_engagement_level
attributes.description: Level of political participation and interest (Disengaged, Single-issue voter, Moderate/occasional participant, Highly engaged partisan).

attributes.name: vote_2024_presidential
attributes.description: Reported 2024 presidential vote choice (Trump, Harris, Third party, Did not vote, Not eligible).

attributes.name: midterm_turnout_propensity
attributes.description: Historical tendency to vote in midterm elections (Always votes, Sometimes votes, Rarely votes, Never votes).

attributes.name: congressional_district_competitiveness
attributes.description: Competitiveness classification of the agent's congressional district (Safe Republican, Lean Republican, Swing district, Lean Democrat, Safe Democrat).

attributes.name: top_issue_2026
attributes.description: Single most salient policy issue heading into the 2026 midterms (Economy/Jobs, Abortion/Reproductive rights, Immigration, Democracy/Rule of law, Healthcare, Climate, Education, AI/Technology).

attributes.name: country_direction_approval
attributes.description: Approval of the current direction of the United States (Strongly approve, Somewhat approve, Somewhat disapprove, Strongly disapprove).

attributes.name: consumer_identity
attributes.description: Primary driver of consumer purchasing behavior (Brand loyal, Price/value driven, Values/ethics driven, Convenience driven).

attributes.name: institutional_trust
attributes.description: General level of trust in major institutions such as government, media, science, and corporations (High trust, Moderate trust, Low trust, Distrustful/Conspiratorial).

attributes.name: openness
attributes.description: Big Five openness to experience: curiosity, creativity, and receptivity to new ideas.

attributes.name: conscientiousness
attributes.description: Big Five conscientiousness: self-discipline, organization, and goal-directed behavior.

attributes.name: extraversion
attributes.description: Big Five extraversion: sociability, assertiveness, and positive affect in social settings.

attributes.name: agreeableness
attributes.description: Big Five agreeableness: cooperativeness, empathy, and tendency toward social harmony.

attributes.name: neuroticism
attributes.description: Big Five neuroticism: emotional instability, anxiety, and susceptibility to stress.

attributes.name: risk_tolerance
attributes.description: General willingness to accept risk in financial, social, and political decisions (0=very risk averse, 1=very risk tolerant).

attributes.name: economic_anxiety
attributes.description: Degree of worry about personal and national economic conditions (0=none, 1=extreme), shaping decision-making under uncertainty.
